					Supervisor, Operations				
Lebanon, TN









Supervisor, Operations
We seek a driven leader to oversee departmental work-flow within our Famous Footwear distribution center operations team in Lebanon, TN.
We are Caleres, a global footwear company with brands that fit people’s lives. We are ferocious about fit and living our mission of helping people feel good, feet first.
Responsibilities:
•	Leadership, training, development and mentorship for Assistant Supervisors, future Assistant Supervisors, as well as, departmental Associates.
•	Maintains a safe, secure and healthy work environment, able to show year-on-year improvements in accident and injury statistics.
•	Ensures company policies are communicated, understood, and administered consistently.
•	Formulation and execution of tactical day-to-day and hour-by-hour operating plans to forecast and plan product flow, and adjust staffing based on volume and service level expectations.
•	Demonstrates team building skills and leads by example.
•	Actively embraces continuous improvement through improvement of self as much as improvement of team, processes and environment.
•	Identify and implement best practices within department and across shifts.
•	Conduct and facilitate operational training, including training across departments within the distribution center.
•	Create a culture of ownership and engagement.
•	Maximizes use of building equipment.
•	Subject matter expert, able to perform research on various exceptions.
•	Partners effectively with own leadership team, as well as with teams and peers off site at other Distribution facilities and at the corporate office.
•	Support of facility operating budget and key project initiatives by validating and achieving engineered standards, and exceeding daily operating goals.
Qualifications:
•	High school diploma or equivalent required
•	Bachelor’s degree in related field preferred
•	2+ years distribution center experience preferred
•	2+ years leadership experience in roles of increasing responsibility preferred
