					Maintenance Technician II				
Lebec, CA









Maintenance Technician II
We seek a focused individual with experience in Distribution Center equipment maintenance and skilled electrical operations to join our Famous Footwear distribution center operations team in Tejon, CA.
We are Caleres, a global footwear company with brands that fit people’s lives. We are passionate about fit and living our mission of helping people feel good, feet first.
We seek people who deliver:
•	Safe and efficient operation of the distribution center equipment by proactive preventive maintenance of equipment, quick reaction to breakdowns so there is minimal mechanical down-time, and insuring all OSHA, NFPA, and other regulatory safety requirements are met or exceeded, including documenting and fire system inspections.
•	Adherence to prescribed processes and procedures to maximize equipment readiness and velocity of product within the distribution center by monitoring interior and exterior of facility and conducting equipment repairs as needed and partnering to fix or update systems when necessary
•	Effective production support, both proactively and reactively through regular monitoring of equipment and following up with equipment users after a repair or system upgrade is implemented
•	Ability to obtain and maintain a PIV (powered industrial vehicle) licenses to operate all PIV equipment associated with the warehouse within 90 days of employment
•	Ability to develop and / or perform welding and fabrication.
•	Basic grounds maintenance and snow shoveling/salting
•	Coordination of efforts between outside contractors and company personnel to accomplish special projects and inspections
•	Coordination of maintenance, PIV, facilities’ and grounds maintenance contractors’ activities
•	Strong knowledge of skilled trades and previous experience working with high-speed conveyance systems and all components
•	Ability to perform mechanical and electrical repairs ranging from routine to advanced on equipment associated with warehouse distribution systems
We seek people with these qualifications:
•	Previous facilities maintenance or maintenance technician experience 3-5 years
•	Previous success in completing mechanical / electrical training programs;  Moderate to advanced mechanical and electrical knowledge base.
•	Training qualifications in maintenance disciplines
•	Knowledge of ARC, MIG and gas welding
•	Must maintain professional demeanor and appearance at all times
•	Ability to lift 50 pounds and physically fit
•	High School Diploma/GED required
But most of all, we seek believers. People who believe remarkable things are possible and will not stop striving for them.
People passionate about their work. People who hold themselves and others accountable. People who think a $2.6 billion company should be as creative as a start-up. People driven by an insatiable curiosity. People who care about being the best, among the best. 
